{
  "stem": "1975.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 198.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were assigned a small two rooms for a family, plus the fact we have some other people who lived in the same-- in the same house.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was one common kitchen for everybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were right away told that we have [BACKROUND NOISE] to start forming a a committee inside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had like a elder, which was Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Elkes, who was the-- the head of the committee.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were some [BACKROUND NOISE] people assigned.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, when we came into the ghetto, we were around 30-- 30,000-some Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we occupied a-- a large section, which was inhabitated by-- it was in a Jewish section, but there were many Lithuanian who lived there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was the famous Slabodka, which, as you know, there was a Slabodka yeshiva was in that part of Kaunas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was like a-- a small suburb.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they pushed in in a-- in a place where you can hold maybe 5,000 people, they pushed in 30- 30,000-some people in that in that place.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The ghetto was walled in, fenced around with barbed wire, and with-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] with policemen and guards surrounded, watching the ghetto, watching the people should not come in.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we didn't have the right to come in and out, except with a-- with a-- with a guard.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This way was instituted the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, in order to-- to make sure that everybody's behaving, what they did is they-- they start putting out some new-- new commands, new befehl.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like, you had to give-- [BACKROUND NOISE] turn in everything from letter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had to turn in all kind of secondary things, which they consider they're also valuable, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what they did is they took one Jew and they hanged him.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
